Source77NW glossary - LSV sample data for the Lookup sample.
This preamble is ignored by the parser: a record begins at a ':'
line, and '.' lines within it carry the value fields. Multi-line
values need no escaping - that is the point of LSV.

:GLOSSARY Source77NW terms
. sample data for samples/Lookup

:LOUD
. Contract violations throw an Issue immediately - misuse of the
. library is never absorbed.

:SOFT
. Absence is a state, not an error: Try*/Got*/Did* surfaces report
. a miss with bool + out instead of throwing.

:Chars
. A struct view (BotIndex, TopIndex) over one base string; scanning
. and parsing move the bounds - no substrings are created.

:Pluck
. Consume from the bottom of a view or stack; Pop consumes from the
. top. Plucked* methods return bool with the value as out.

:ItemStack
. A sliding-window stack that is also a cheap queue: Push, Pop
. (LIFO), Pluck (FIFO), Sort, BinarySearch - a bare-metal core.

:Issue
. The single application exception: Kind + Source + Spot pack into
. HResult; handling dispatches on Kind, not on exception type.

:Spot
. A byte pinning the exact raise site within a module's issueSource.

:ARHSCE
. FileAttr's six-char dot format: Archive ReadOnly Hidden System
. Compressed Encrypted.

:LSV
. Line Separated Values: ':' begins a record, '.' begins a field
. line - multi-line values need no escaping.

:Agent
. The wrapping layer that adds locking, async, and validation around
. a bare-metal core (StackAgent around ItemStack).
